-- Italy to Propose Changes to Business Incentives, Tax Breaks, Corriere Says
-- B y   A r m o r e l   K e n n a
-- 2010-11-25T07:10:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-25/italy-to-propose-changes-to-business-incentives-tax-breaks-corriere-says.html
Italian Industry Minister  Paolo Romani  said he will present proposals next week to change
business tax breaks and incentives, daily Corriere della Sera
reported, citing an interview.  The government wants to simplify the process, Romani told
the Italian newspaper, adding that country has 100 different
types of national incentives aimed at spurring consumer
purchases of products.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Armorel Kenna  in Milan at 
 akenna@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
